body: Adding the *Ref APIs make sense to allow users to use the strong reference APIs from the Cython side. I'm gonna follow up with `PyList` APIs as well, if this is okay with you all.

comment_data.body:
We generally spell this with a lower-case `d` because `D` is easily confused with `0` in some fonts.
```suggestion
    #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030d0000
```
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -3,11 +3,91 @@ from .pyport cimport uint64_t
 
 cdef extern from *:
     # On Python 2, PyDict_GetItemWithError is called _PyDict_GetItemWithError
+    # Also backport PyDict_GetItemStringRef and PyDict_SetDefaultRef
     """
     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION <= 2
     #define PyDict_GetItemWithError _PyDict_GetItemWithError
     #endif
+
+    #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030D0000

@@ -3,11 +3,95 @@ from .pyport cimport uint64_t
 
 cdef extern from *:
     # On Python 2, PyDict_GetItemWithError is called _PyDict_GetItemWithError

comment_data.body: I don't think we'll remember that there is something near the end (and probably somewhere in the middle of the file at some point) that sets `__doc__` to a fixed value. Either move it to the top, or set `__doc__ = ''` at the top and use `+=` here, to make sure we don't accidentally lose future docstrings at the top without noticing.

@@ -37,3 +42,34 @@ def test_gilstate():
     # TODO assert that GIL is taken
     PyGILState_Release(gstate)
     return 'ok'
+
+def test_dict_getref(d):
+    """
+    >>> test_dict_getref({'key': ['value']})
+    ['value']
+    ['value']
+    1 ['value']
+    >>> test_dict_getref({})
+    0 Ellipsis
+
+    One further test is in the module __doc__ to exclude it for PyPy
+    """
+    cdef PyObject* o;
+    if PyDict_GetItemRef(d, "key", &o):
+        print(<object>o)
+        Py_XDECREF(o)
+    
+    if PyDict_GetItemStringRef(d, "key", &o):
+        print(<object>o)
+        Py_XDECREF(o)
+    
+    was_in_dict = PyDict_SetDefaultRef(d, "key", Ellipsis, &o)
+    print(was_in_dict, <object>o)
+    Py_XDECREF(o)
+
+if not hasattr(sys, 'pypy_version_info'):
+    __doc__ = """

comment_data.body: I agree but I did it in https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/7367 to try to keep this change doing one thing

Fixes and add tests

   utility code to avoid conflicts
4. Add tests
